FL,415,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41402
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F414A1771927474
OL,3,CTwo men jailed for 'disturbing'
OL,4,Ckilling of sheep
OL,6,FAfter catching one of the animals,
OL,7,Fthey launched a violent assault, using
OL,8,Fexplosive 'bangers' to inflict fatal
OL,9,Finjuries.
OL,11,FThe investigation was launched after
OL,12,Fthe attack was reported to Sussex
OL,13,FPolice. Both men were arrested two
OL,14,Fdays later.
OL,16,FDuring the investigation, officers
OL,17,Ffound footage of Ashby carrying out
OL,18,Fthe attack on Hollands' mobile phone.
OL,19,FIt also contained videos of an
OL,20,Funidentified person attacking both
OL,21,Flive and deceased animals.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/4
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,415,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F414A1771927474
OL,3,CTwo men jailed for 'disturbing'
OL,4,Ckilling of sheep
OL,6,FPolice also found the sheep's ear
OL,7,Ftags, which Ashby had taken from the
OL,8,Fscene, at a nearby property.
OL,10,FBoth men pleaded guilty to charges of
OL,11,Fcausing unnecessary suffering to a
OL,12,Fprotected animal during a hearing at
OL,13,FBrighton Magistrates' Court in August
OL,14,F2025.
OL,16,FAt the sentencing on Monday Leighton
OL,17,FAshby, of Beckett Road in Ashford, was
OL,18,Fjailed for two years, and Oakley
OL,19,FHollands, of Mussenden Lane in Horton
OL,20,FKirby, was sentenced to 20 months in a
OL,21,Fyoung offenders' institute.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/4
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,415,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F414A1771927474
OL,3,CTwo men jailed for 'disturbing'
OL,4,Ckilling of sheep
OL,6,FFollowing the sentencing,
OL,7,FSuperintendent Rachel Swinney of
OL,8,FSussex Police praised the seriousness
OL,9,Fwith which the case was handled: "This
OL,10,Fwas a disturbing incident that has
OL,11,Fbeen treated with the seriousness it
OL,12,Fdeserved.
OL,14,F"Both of these men have now faced
OL,15,Fjustice for their crimes, which should
OL,16,Fsend a clear message that we will
OL,17,Fprotect our rural communities and hold
OL,18,Foffenders to account."
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/4
